  "why": "The paper's method (DRFuzz) is explicitly designed to find regression faults defined as inputs where the new model misclassifies an input that the prior model classified correctly — i.e., prediction/misprediction differences. The evaluation is performed on standard image-classification datasets (MNIST, CIFAR10, Fashion-MNIST, SVHN) and measures counts of regression-triggering inputs and misclassification behaviors. The paper does not target models equipped with explicit safety, policy, or security safeguards, nor does it demonstrate any empirical bypassing of such safeguards or finding harmful/unsafe/toxic behaviors. Therefore the failures discovered are robustness-related mispredictions rather than security- or policy-bypass incidents, which matches the metric's \"Low\" class.",
